Output

The Smart Cleaning Robot produces the following results during operation:
Effective removal of dust and debris using rotating brushes and vacuum suction
Successful wet cleaning of stains through water spraying and wiping mechanism
Proper drying of the floor using the dry wipe system
Smooth and autonomous navigation with obstacle avoidance
Continuous monitoring of battery status through LED display
Reliable and consistent cleaning performance across indoor environments

Demonstration
The working of the Smart Cleaning Robot can be demonstrated in the following steps:
Power ON the robot using the ON/OFF button
The system initializes sensors and components
Robot begins autonomous movement
Sensors detect obstacles and adjust direction accordingly
Cleaning mechanisms activate simultaneously:
Brushes sweep dust
Vacuum collects debris
Water pump sprays water
Wet wipe cleans surface
Dry wipe dries the floor
Robot continues operation until the area is cleaned or battery is low

Testing Scenarios
Obstacle Test: Robot successfully detects and avoids objects like walls and furniture
Dry Cleaning Test: Dust and small particles are effectively collected
Wet Cleaning Test: Stains are removed using water and wiping system
Navigation Test: Smooth movement in different directions without collision
Battery Test: System displays accurate battery level

Expected Result
Clean and dry floor surface
Reduced human effort
Time-efficient cleaning process
Stable and reliable system performance
